# Data Migrations

All data migrations (Firestore document rewrites, UID remaps, schema changes, backfills, etc.) must be run as **one-time local scripts** — never as part of the deployed codebase.

## Rules

- Create a standalone Node.js script in `server/` (e.g. `server/migrate-xyz.js`)
- Use `firebase-admin` SDK with local credentials (`GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS` or gcloud default)
- Run the script locally with `node migrate-xyz.js`
- Make the script **idempotent** — safe to run multiple times without duplicating data
- Log progress clearly so the operator can verify correctness
- Delete the script after successful execution (do not commit it)

## Why

Embedding migration logic in application code (e.g. inside API endpoints or middleware) creates fragile, hard-to-remove code paths that run on every request. One-time scripts are simpler, auditable, and disposable.
